{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Tt23We9wvqC2426P4KonwS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Cloche Usage\n     2→\n     3→Cloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\n     4→workflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\n     5→container, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\n     6→results to a git branch.\n     7→\n     8→## Core Concepts\n     9→\n    10→- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n    11→- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n    12→- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n    13→- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n    14→- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n    15→\n    16→## Workflow DSL\n    17→\n    18→Workflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\n    19→declared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\n    20→no orphans, entry point exists).\n    21→\n    22→### Minimal Example\n    23→\n    24→```\n    25→workflow \"develop\" {\n    26→  step implement {\n    27→    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    28→    results = [success, fail]\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  step test {\n    32→    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    33→    results = [success, fail]\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  implement:success -> test\n    37→  implement:fail -> abort\n    38→  test:success -> done\n    39→  test:fail -> abort\n    40→}\n    41→```\n    42→\n    43→### Step Configuration\n    44→\n    45→| Key | Type | Description |\n    46→|-----|------|-------------|\n    47→| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n    48→| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n    49→| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n    50→| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n    51→| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n    52→| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n    53→| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n    54→| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n    55→| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n    56→| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n    57→\n    58→A step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n    59→\n    60→### The `file()` Function\n    61→\n    62→`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n    63→(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\n    64→templates:\n    65→\n    66→```\n    67→prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    68→```\n    69→\n    70→### The `container {}` Block\n    71→\n    72→Can appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n    73→\n    74→**Step level** — per-step container config:\n    75→```\n    76→step code {\n    77→  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    78→  container {\n    79→    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    80→    memory        = \"4g\"\n    81→    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n    82→  }\n    83→  results = [success, fail]\n    84→}\n    85→```\n    86→\n    87→**Workflow level** — defaults for all steps:\n    88→```\n    89→workflow \"develop\" {\n    90→  container {\n    91→    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    92→    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    93→    memory        = \"4g\"\n    94→  }\n    95→  ...\n    96→}\n    97→```\n    98→\n    99→Supported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n   100→\n   101→### The `host {}` Block\n   102→\n   103→Can appear at workflow level in host workflows (`.cloche/host.cloche`). Keys are stored\n   104→with a `host.` prefix. Configures agent defaults for agent steps running on the host.\n   105→\n   106→```\n   107→workflow \"main\" {\n   108→  host {\n   109→    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   110→  }\n   111→  ...\n   112→}\n   113→```\n   114→\n   115→Supported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`. Step-level `agent_command` and\n   116→`agent_args` config keys override the workflow-level `host {}` defaults.\n   117→\n   118→### Wiring Syntax\n   119→\n   120→Connect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n   121→\n   122→```\n   123→implement:success -> test\n   124→implement:fail -> abort\n   125→test:success -> done\n   126→test:fail -> fix\n   127→```\n   128→\n   129→### Wire Output Mappings\n   130→\n   131→Extract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n   132→\n   133→```\n   134→step-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n   135→```\n   136→\n   137→Path expressions:\n   138→\n   139→| Expression | Meaning |\n   140→|---|---|\n   141→| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n   142→| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n   143→| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n   144→| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n   145→| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n   146→\n   147→If the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\n   148→text, only bare `output` works.\n   149→\n   150→### Retry Loops\n   151→\n   152→Wire failures back to earlier steps:\n   153→\n   154→```\n   155→test:fail -> fix\n   156→fix:success -> test    // retry the test\n   157→fix:fail -> abort\n   158→```\n   159→\n   160→Use `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n   161→\n   162→```\n   163→step fix {\n   164→  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n   165→  max_attempts = \"2\"\n   166→  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   167→}\n   168→```\n   169→\n   170→### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n   171→\n   172→Wire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n   173→\n   174→```\n   175→test:success -> lint\n   176→test:success -> quality\n   177→```\n   178→\n   179→### Collect (Join)\n   180→\n   181→Synchronize parallel branches:\n   182→\n   183→```\n   184→collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   185→collect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   186→```\n   187→\n   188→`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n   189→\n   190→### Comments\n   191→\n   192→Line comments with `//`:\n   193→\n   194→```\n   195→// This is a comment\n   196→implement:success -> test  // inline comment\n   197→```\n   198→\n   199→## Result Protocol\n   200→\n   201→Steps report results by printing a marker line to stdout:\n   202→\n   203→```\n   204→CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n   205→```\n   206→\n   207→For example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n   208→\n   209→Rules:\n   210→- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n   211→- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n   212→- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n   213→- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n   214→- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n   215→\n   216→## Prompt Assembly\n   217→\n   218→When an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n   219→\n   220→1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n   221→2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n   222→3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n   223→4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n   224→\n   225→The assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n   226→\n   227→## Agent Command Resolution\n   228→\n   229→Priority (highest to lowest):\n   230→1. Step-level `agent_command`\n   231→2. Workflow-level config block (`container { agent_command }` for container workflows, `host { agent_command }` for host workflows)\n   232→3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n   233→4. Default: `claude`\n   234→\n   235→### Fallback Chains\n   236→\n   237→Comma-separated commands are tried in order:\n   238→\n   239→```\n   240→agent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n   241→```\n   242→\n   243→- **Command not found / failed to start** — try next command\n   244→- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — try next command\n   245→- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — use that result (no fallback)\n   246→- **Exit 0** — use result (no fallback)\n   247→- **All commands fail to start** — step returns an error\n   248→- **Last command crashes without marker** — step returns `fail`\n   249→\n   250→Known agents (e.g. `claude`) get default arguments (`-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`). Unknown agents receive the prompt on stdin with no flags. Override with `agent_args`.\n   251→\n   252→## Workflow Locations\n   253→\n   254→**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\n   255→via `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n   256→\n   257→**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\n   258→Steps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\n   259→dispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes. Script steps\n   260→execute with their working directory set to the main git worktree, so host-workflow\n   261→fixes on main are available to in-flight runs even if they branched earlier.\n   262→\n   263→A single `host.cloche` file may contain **multiple named workflows**. The daemon\n   264→uses up to three workflow phases for orchestration:\n   265→\n   266→| Phase | Workflow name | Purpose |\n   267→|-------|--------------|---------|\n   268→| 1 | `list-tasks` | Discover available work. Output is JSONL (one task per line). |\n   269→| 2 | `main` | Do the work. Receives a task ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var. |\n   270→| 3 | `finalize` | Post-main cleanup. Runs on **both** success and failure. |\n   271→\n   272→Only `main` is required. If `list-tasks` is absent, the daemon uses a single-workflow\n   273→mode. If `finalize` is absent, it is skipped.\n   274→\n   275→### list-tasks Output Format\n   276→\n   277→The `list-tasks` workflow's final step output is parsed as JSONL. Each line is a JSON\n   278→object:\n   279→\n   280→| Field | Required | Description |\n   281→|-------|----------|-------------|\n   282→| `id` | yes | Unique task identifier |\n   283→| `status` | yes | One of `open`, `closed`, `in-progress` |\n   284→| `title` | no | Short summary |\n   285→| `description` | no | Full description |\n   286→| `metadata` | no | Arbitrary key-value pairs |\n   287→\n   288→The daemon picks the first task with status `open`, runs `main` with that task's ID\n   289→set in `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, then runs `finalize` with the outcome. Tasks are\n   290→deduplicated within a timeout window to prevent rapid reassignment of the same task.\n   291→\n   292→### Host Workflow Example\n   293→\n   294→A three-phase `host.cloche`:\n   295→\n   296→```\n   297→workflow \"list-tasks\" {\n   298→  step fetch-tickets {\n   299→    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\n   300→    results = [success, fail]\n   301→  }\n   302→\n   303→  fetch-tickets:success -> done\n   304→  fetch-tickets:fail    -> abort\n   305→}\n   306→\n   307→workflow \"main\" {\n   308→  host {\n   309→    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   310→  }\n   311→\n   312→  step prepare-prompt {\n   313→    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n   314→    results = [success, fail]\n   315→  }\n   316→\n   317→  step develop {\n   318→    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n   319→    results       = [success, fail]\n   320→  }\n   321→\n   322→  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n   323→  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n   324→  develop:success        -> done\n   325→  develop:fail           -> done\n   326→}\n   327→\n   328→workflow \"finalize\" {\n   329→  step push-for-review {\n   330→    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/push-for-review.sh\"\n   331→    results = [success, fail]\n   332→  }\n   333→\n   334→  push-for-review:success -> done\n   335→  push-for-review:fail    -> done\n   336→}\n   337→```\n   338→\n   339→The `list-tasks` script writes JSONL to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`. The `main` workflow\n   340→receives the task ID and is responsible for claiming the ticket. The `finalize`\n   341→workflow receives `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` env vars to decide\n   342→what cleanup to perform.\n   343→\n   344→### Host Step Environment Variables\n   345→\n   346→| Variable | Description |\n   347→|----------|-------------|\n   348→| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n   349→| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n   350→| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the output file from the immediately preceding step. |\n   351→| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n   352→| `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` | Task ID assigned by the daemon (set for `main` and `finalize` phases). |\n   353→| `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` | Result of the `main` workflow (`succeeded` or `failed`). Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n   354→| `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` | Run ID of the completed `main` workflow. Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n   355→| Wire-mapped vars | Any env vars declared in wire output mappings. |\n   356→\n   357→### Container Environment Variables\n   358→\n   359→| Variable | Description |\n   360→|----------|-------------|\n   361→| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n   362→| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n   363→| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n   364→\n   365→## Complete Example: Container Workflow with Parallel Validation\n   366→\n   367→```\n   368→workflow \"develop\" {\n   369→  step implement {\n   370→    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n   371→    results = [success, fail]\n   372→  }\n   373→\n   374→  step test {\n   375→    run = \"bundle exec rake test 2>&1\"\n   376→    results = [success, fail]\n   377→  }\n   378→\n   379→  step lint {\n   380→    run = \"bundle exec rubocop 2>&1\"\n   381→    results = [success, fail]\n   382→  }\n   383→\n   384→  step quality {\n   385→    run = \"python3 scripts/quality-check.py 2>&1\"\n   386→    results = [success, fail]\n   387→  }\n   388→\n   389→  step fix {\n   390→    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n   391→    max_attempts = \"2\"\n   392→    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   393→  }\n   394→\n   395→  implement:success -> test\n   396→  implement:fail -> abort\n   397→\n   398→  test:success -> lint\n   399→  test:success -> quality\n   400→  test:fail -> fix\n   401→\n   402→  lint:fail -> fix\n   403→  quality:fail -> fix\n   404→  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   405→\n   406→  fix:success -> test\n   407→  fix:fail -> abort\n   408→  fix:give-up -> abort\n   409→}\n   410→```\n   411→\n   412→## Container Isolation Model\n   413→\n   414→- **Files in**: `docker cp` copies the project into `/workspace/`. No bind mounts. Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on top. `.git/` is included.\n   415→- **Files out**: On completion, the daemon extracts results via `docker cp` into a git worktree and commits to a `cloche/<run-id>` branch.\n   416→- **Auth mounts**: `~/.claude` and `~/.claude.json` are bind-mounted read-only for Claude Code session reuse.\n   417→- **Network**: Containers have network access (needed for API calls).\n   418→- **Cleanup**: Containers are removed after successful runs unless `--keep-container` is set. Failed runs always keep their container.\n   419→\n   420→Your project directory is never modified by the container.\n   421→\n   422→## CLI Reference\n   423→\n   424→### `cloche init`\n   425→\n   426→Scaffold a new Cloche project.\n   427→\n   428→```\n   429→cloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n   430→```\n   431→\n   432→| Flag | Default | Description |\n   433→|------|---------|-------------|\n   434→| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name. Creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   435→| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for the generated Dockerfile. |\n   436→\n   437→Creates `.cloche/` with workflow file, Dockerfile, `config.toml`, prompt templates,\n   438→host workflow (`host.cloche`), and prompt generation script. Skips existing files.\n   439→\n   440→### `cloche run`\n   441→\n   442→Launch a workflow run.\n   443→\n   444→```\n   445→cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n   446→```\n   447→\n   448→| Flag | Description |\n   449→|------|-------------|\n   450→| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   451→| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n   452→| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n   453→| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n   454→\n   455→Must be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\n   456→when `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n   457→\n   458→### `cloche status`\n   459→\n   460→```\n   461→cloche status <run-id>\n   462→```\n   463→\n   464→Shows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n   465→\n   466→### `cloche list`\n   467→\n   468→```\n   469→cloche list [--all]\n   470→```\n   471→\n   472→Lists runs from the last hour (or all with `--all`).\n   473→\n   474→### `cloche logs`\n   475→\n   476→```\n   477→cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n   478→```\n   479→\n   480→| Flag | Description |\n   481→|------|-------------|\n   482→| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n   483→| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n   484→| `--follow`, `-f` | Stream live logs via SSE with color-coded output (requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`). |\n   485→\n   486→For active runs, `cloche logs <run-id>` streams LLM output and step status in real time via gRPC (no `--follow` needed). For completed runs, it serves the saved log files.\n   487→\n   488→### `cloche poll`\n   489→\n   490→```\n   491→cloche poll <run-id>\n   492→```\n   493→\n   494→Block until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n   495→\n   496→### `cloche stop`\n   497→\n   498→```\n   499→cloche stop <run-id>\n   500→```\n   501→\n   502→### `cloche delete`\n   503→\n   504→```\n   505→cloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n   506→```\n   507→\n   508→Delete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n   509→\n   510→### `cloche health`\n   511→\n   512→```\n   513→cloche health\n   514→```\n   515→\n   516→Show per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n   517→\n   518→### `cloche get`\n   519→\n   520→```\n   521→cloche get <key>\n   522→```\n   523→\n   524→Get a value from the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\n   525→the `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\n   526→the current working directory. Exits 1 if the key is not found.\n   527→\n   528→### `cloche set`\n   529→\n   530→```\n   531→cloche set <key> <value>\n   532→```\n   533→\n   534→Set a value in the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\n   535→the `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\n   536→the current working directory. Creates the file and directories if they don't exist.\n   537→\n   538→### `cloche tasks`\n   539→\n   540→```\n   541→cloche tasks [--project <dir>]\n   542→```\n   543→\n   544→Show the task pipeline and assignment state for an orchestration loop. Displays\n   545→upcoming/open tasks, which tasks are assigned to which runs, and auto-assignment\n   546→state. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP` (talks to the daemon's web API).\n   547→\n   548→| Flag | Default | Description |\n   549→|------|---------|-------------|\n   550→| `--project <dir>` | current directory name | Project to query tasks for. |\n   551→\n   552→### `cloche shutdown`\n   553→\n   554→```\n   555→cloche shutdown\n   556→```\n   557→\n   558→## Project Layout\n   559→\n   560→```\n   561→my-project/\n   562→├── .cloche/\n   563→│   ├── develop.cloche        # Container workflow\n   564→│   ├── host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\n   565→│   ├── Dockerfile            # Container image definition\n   566→│   ├── config.toml           # Project configuration\n   567→│   ├── prompts/              # Prompt templates\n   568→│   │   ├── implement.md\n   569→│   │   ├── fix.md\n   570→│   │   └── update-docs.md\n   571→│   ├── scripts/              # Host-side scripts\n   572→│   ├── overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\n   573→│   │   └── CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\n   574→│   └── <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\n   575→│       ├── prompt.txt        # User prompt\n   576→│       ├── context.json      # Shared key-value store (cloche get/set)\n   577→│       ├── output/\n   578→│       │   ├── full.log      # Unified log\n   579→│       │   ├── test.log      # Per-step script output\n   580→│       │   └── llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\n   581→│       ├── attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\n   582→│       └── history.log       # Step execution log\n   583→├── src/                      # Project source (untouched by Cloche)\n   584→└── .git/\n   585→```\n   586→\n   587→## Daemon Configuration\n   588→\n   589→| Variable | Default | Description |\n   590→|----------|---------|-------------|\n   591→| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n   592→| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n   593→| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n   594→| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n   595→| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n   596→| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n   597→| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n   598→| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n   599→| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n   600→| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n   601→\n   602→### Client Configuration\n   603→\n   604→| Variable | Default | Description |\n   605→|----------|---------|-------------|\n   606→| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n   607→| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n   608→\n   609→## Dockerfile Requirements\n   610→\n   611→The container image must have:\n   612→- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n   613→- `git` installed\n   614→- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n   615→- `/workspace` as the working directory\n   616→- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n   617→\n   618→## Build Commands\n   619→\n   620→```\n   621→make build          # Build all binaries to bin/\n   622→make test           # Run all tests\n   623→make test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\n   624→make lint           # Run go vet\n   625→make proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\n   626→make docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\n   627→make install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\n   628→make clean          # Remove bin/\n   629→```\n   630→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"32a9924e-c776-408c-8085-162da40f446c","uuid":"6e37424c-1920-496f-8471-00a57cf5c7fc","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"# Cloche Usage\n\nCloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\nworkflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\ncontainer, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\nresults to a git branch.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n\n## Workflow DSL\n\nWorkflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\ndeclared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\nno orphans, entry point exists).\n\n### Minimal Example\n\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n  test:success -> done\n  test:fail -> abort\n}\n```\n\n### Step Configuration\n\n| Key | Type | Description |\n|-----|------|-------------|\n| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n\nA step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n\n### The `file()` Function\n\n`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\ntemplates:\n\n```\nprompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n```\n\n### The `container {}` Block\n\nCan appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n\n**Step level** — per-step container config:\n```\nstep code {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n  container {\n    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n  }\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n**Workflow level** — defaults for all steps:\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  container {\n    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nSupported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n\n### The `host {}` Block\n\nCan appear at workflow level in host workflows (`.cloche/host.cloche`). Keys are stored\nwith a `host.` prefix. Configures agent defaults for agent steps running on the host.\n\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  host {\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nSupported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`. Step-level `agent_command` and\n`agent_args` config keys override the workflow-level `host {}` defaults.\n\n### Wiring Syntax\n\nConnect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n\n```\nimplement:success -> test\nimplement:fail -> abort\ntest:success -> done\ntest:fail -> fix\n```\n\n### Wire Output Mappings\n\nExtract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n\n```\nstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n```\n\nPath expressions:\n\n| Expression | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n\nIf the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\ntext, only bare `output` works.\n\n### Retry Loops\n\nWire failures back to earlier steps:\n\n```\ntest:fail -> fix\nfix:success -> test    // retry the test\nfix:fail -> abort\n```\n\nUse `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n\n```\nstep fix {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n  max_attempts = \"2\"\n  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n}\n```\n\n### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n\nWire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n\n```\ntest:success -> lint\ntest:success -> quality\n```\n\n### Collect (Join)\n\nSynchronize parallel branches:\n\n```\ncollect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\ncollect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n```\n\n`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n\n### Comments\n\nLine comments with `//`:\n\n```\n// This is a comment\nimplement:success -> test  // inline comment\n```\n\n## Result Protocol\n\nSteps report results by printing a marker line to stdout:\n\n```\nCLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n```\n\nFor example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n\nRules:\n- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n\n## Prompt Assembly\n\nWhen an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n\n1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n\nThe assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n\n## Agent Command Resolution\n\nPriority (highest to lowest):\n1. Step-level `agent_command`\n2. Workflow-level config block (`container { agent_command }` for container workflows, `host { agent_command }` for host workflows)\n3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n4. Default: `claude`\n\n### Fallback Chains\n\nComma-separated commands are tried in order:\n\n```\nagent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n```\n\n- **Command not found / failed to start** — try next command\n- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — try next command\n- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — use that result (no fallback)\n- **Exit 0** — use result (no fallback)\n- **All commands fail to start** — step returns an error\n- **Last command crashes without marker** — step returns `fail`\n\nKnown agents (e.g. `claude`) get default arguments (`-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`). Unknown agents receive the prompt on stdin with no flags. Override with `agent_args`.\n\n## Workflow Locations\n\n**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\nvia `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n\n**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\nSteps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\ndispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes. Script steps\nexecute with their working directory set to the main git worktree, so host-workflow\nfixes on main are available to in-flight runs even if they branched earlier.\n\nA single `host.cloche` file may contain **multiple named workflows**. The daemon\nuses up to three workflow phases for orchestration:\n\n| Phase | Workflow name | Purpose |\n|-------|--------------|---------|\n| 1 | `list-tasks` | Discover available work. Output is JSONL (one task per line). |\n| 2 | `main` | Do the work. Receives a task ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var. |\n| 3 | `finalize` | Post-main cleanup. Runs on **both** success and failure. |\n\nOnly `main` is required. If `list-tasks` is absent, the daemon uses a single-workflow\nmode. If `finalize` is absent, it is skipped.\n\n### list-tasks Output Format\n\nThe `list-tasks` workflow's final step output is parsed as JSONL. Each line is a JSON\nobject:\n\n| Field | Required | Description |\n|-------|----------|-------------|\n| `id` | yes | Unique task identifier |\n| `status` | yes | One of `open`, `closed`, `in-progress` |\n| `title` | no | Short summary |\n| `description` | no | Full description |\n| `metadata` | no | Arbitrary key-value pairs |\n\nThe daemon picks the first task with status `open`, runs `main` with that task's ID\nset in `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, then runs `finalize` with the outcome. Tasks are\ndeduplicated within a timeout window to prevent rapid reassignment of the same task.\n\n### Host Workflow Example\n\nA three-phase `host.cloche`:\n\n```\nworkflow \"list-tasks\" {\n  step fetch-tickets {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  fetch-tickets:success -> done\n  fetch-tickets:fail    -> abort\n}\n\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  host {\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n  }\n\n  step prepare-prompt {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step develop {\n    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    results       = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n  develop:success        -> done\n  develop:fail           -> done\n}\n\nworkflow \"finalize\" {\n  step push-for-review {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/push-for-review.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  push-for-review:success -> done\n  push-for-review:fail    -> done\n}\n```\n\nThe `list-tasks` script writes JSONL to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`. The `main` workflow\nreceives the task ID and is responsible for claiming the ticket. The `finalize`\nworkflow receives `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` env vars to decide\nwhat cleanup to perform.\n\n### Host Step Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the output file from the immediately preceding step. |\n| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n| `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` | Task ID assigned by the daemon (set for `main` and `finalize` phases). |\n| `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` | Result of the `main` workflow (`succeeded` or `failed`). Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n| `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` | Run ID of the completed `main` workflow. Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n| Wire-mapped vars | Any env vars declared in wire output mappings. |\n\n### Container Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n\n## Complete Example: Container Workflow with Parallel Validation\n\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"bundle exec rake test 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step lint {\n    run = \"bundle exec rubocop 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step quality {\n    run = \"python3 scripts/quality-check.py 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step fix {\n    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n    max_attempts = \"2\"\n    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n\n  test:success -> lint\n  test:success -> quality\n  test:fail -> fix\n\n  lint:fail -> fix\n  quality:fail -> fix\n  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n\n  fix:success -> test\n  fix:fail -> abort\n  fix:give-up -> abort\n}\n```\n\n## Container Isolation Model\n\n- **Files in**: `docker cp` copies the project into `/workspace/`. No bind mounts. Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on top. `.git/` is included.\n- **Files out**: On completion, the daemon extracts results via `docker cp` into a git worktree and commits to a `cloche/<run-id>` branch.\n- **Auth mounts**: `~/.claude` and `~/.claude.json` are bind-mounted read-only for Claude Code session reuse.\n- **Network**: Containers have network access (needed for API calls).\n- **Cleanup**: Containers are removed after successful runs unless `--keep-container` is set. Failed runs always keep their container.\n\nYour project directory is never modified by the container.\n\n## CLI Reference\n\n### `cloche init`\n\nScaffold a new Cloche project.\n\n```\ncloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n```\n\n| Flag | Default | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name. Creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for the generated Dockerfile. |\n\nCreates `.cloche/` with workflow file, Dockerfile, `config.toml`, prompt templates,\nhost workflow (`host.cloche`), and prompt generation script. Skips existing files.\n\n### `cloche run`\n\nLaunch a workflow run.\n\n```\ncloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n\nMust be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\nwhen `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n\n### `cloche status`\n\n```\ncloche status <run-id>\n```\n\nShows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n\n### `cloche list`\n\n```\ncloche list [--all]\n```\n\nLists runs from the last hour (or all with `--all`).\n\n### `cloche logs`\n\n```\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n| `--follow`, `-f` | Stream live logs via SSE with color-coded output (requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`). |\n\nFor active runs, `cloche logs <run-id>` streams LLM output and step status in real time via gRPC (no `--follow` needed). For completed runs, it serves the saved log files.\n\n### `cloche poll`\n\n```\ncloche poll <run-id>\n```\n\nBlock until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n\n### `cloche stop`\n\n```\ncloche stop <run-id>\n```\n\n### `cloche delete`\n\n```\ncloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n```\n\nDelete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n\n### `cloche health`\n\n```\ncloche health\n```\n\nShow per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n\n### `cloche get`\n\n```\ncloche get <key>\n```\n\nGet a value from the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\nthe `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\nthe current working directory. Exits 1 if the key is not found.\n\n### `cloche set`\n\n```\ncloche set <key> <value>\n```\n\nSet a value in the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\nthe `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\nthe current working directory. Creates the file and directories if they don't exist.\n\n### `cloche tasks`\n\n```\ncloche tasks [--project <dir>]\n```\n\nShow the task pipeline and assignment state for an orchestration loop. Displays\nupcoming/open tasks, which tasks are assigned to which runs, and auto-assignment\nstate. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP` (talks to the daemon's web API).\n\n| Flag | Default | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--project <dir>` | current directory name | Project to query tasks for. |\n\n### `cloche shutdown`\n\n```\ncloche shutdown\n```\n\n## Project Layout\n\n```\nmy-project/\n├── .cloche/\n│   ├── develop.cloche        # Container workflow\n│   ├── host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\n│   ├── Dockerfile            # Container image definition\n│   ├── config.toml           # Project configuration\n│   ├── prompts/              # Prompt templates\n│   │   ├── implement.md\n│   │   ├── fix.md\n│   │   └── update-docs.md\n│   ├── scripts/              # Host-side scripts\n│   ├── overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\n│   │   └── CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\n│   └── <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\n│       ├── prompt.txt        # User prompt\n│       ├── context.json      # Shared key-value store (cloche get/set)\n│       ├── output/\n│       │   ├── full.log      # Unified log\n│       │   ├── test.log      # Per-step script output\n│       │   └── llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\n│       ├── attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\n│       └── history.log       # Step execution log\n├── src/                      # Project source (untouched by Cloche)\n└── .git/\n```\n\n## Daemon Configuration\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n\n### Client Configuration\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n\n## Dockerfile Requirements\n\nThe container image must have:\n- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n- `git` installed\n- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n- `/workspace` as the working directory\n- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n\n## Build Commands\n\n```\nmake build          # Build all binaries to bin/\nmake test           # Run all tests\nmake test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\nmake lint           # Run go vet\nmake proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\nmake docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\nmake install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\nmake clean          # Remove bin/\n```\n","numLines":630,"startLine":1,"totalLines":630}}}
